There was a further motion in a related matter also seeking that I recuse myself. There, the only issue for determination was the question of costs. The motion was, by consent, discontinued on 23 March 2009. I then delivered judgment in the matter: Australian Securities & Investment Commission v Bowesco [2009] FCA 257. History of proceeding

The proceedings were instituted in early 2006. The trial of the action took place over three days between 25 and 27 March 2008.

Thereafter there were further hearings in respect to the case on the following dates: 
 (i) 11 April 2008;
 (ii) 11 June 2008;
 (iii) 8 August 2008;
 (iv) 3 September 2008;
 (v) 13 November 2008;
 (vi) 10 February 2009.
